description:
@15:58 "Changes in cultural values will prompt people to recognize the underlying economic reality but, conversely, cultural values can completely blind people to economic reality, and prevent them from making the right decision."

Many left-wing vegans presume an antipathy between capitalism and veganism, but is there, perhaps, "an economic approach to veganism" embracing the relative efficiency (and profitability) of vegan products in free market competition?

This video is "vs. ModVegan" to some extent, and you can find her channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCXwREs2xdJSI0Zj9nL2MzKA/videos

And, yes, as mentioned, you can click through to my Patreon to join the conversation: https://www.patreon.com/a_bas_le_ciel
